OL,4,Cbefore son's death, inquest hears
OL,6,FDuring the third day of the inquest
OL,7,Finto his death Charlie's social worker
OL,8,FNicky Herbert admitted a more
OL,9,Fexperienced professional should have
OL,10,Fbeen in charge.
OL,12,FGiving evidence to the jury inquest at
OL,13,FRochdale Coroners Coutr, Ms Herbert
OL,14,Fexplained she had only been in the job
OL,15,Ffor two years, and said Charlie had
OL,16,Fthe most complex needs of all of her
OL,17,F20 cases.
