OL,3,CMother 'pleaded' for more support
OL,4,Cbefore son's death, inquest hears
OL,6,FHis social worker Nicky Herbert told
OL,7,Fthe coroner that this was a "major red
OL,8,Fflag" - however acknowledged that
OL,9,FCharlie could not go home without more
OL,10,Fsupport and Trafford Council were
OL,11,Funable to find him a better placement
OL,12,For foster care.
OL,14,FThe inquest could last up to three
OL,15,Fweeks, with the jury looking to answer
OL,16,Fwhether Charlie meant to take his own
OL,17,Flife.
